Key Match Events: Keyonte George had 33 points and nine assists, leading the Utah Jazz to their first win of the season.
John Collins added 28 points and 13 rebounds for the Jazz.
Collin Sexton contributed 24 points for Utah.
Walker Kessler had 12 points and 15 rebounds for the Jazz.
Coby White scored 28 points for the Chicago Bulls, tying the game twice late in the third quarter.
Ayo Dosunmu scored 25 points on 9-for-13 shooting for Chicago.
Nikola Vucevic had 23 points for the Bulls.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Jazz had a season high in points.
Keyonte George, in his second NBA season, tied his career high in points.
